    'queens-indian': {



      overview: "<p>The Queen's Indian is the Nimzo's natural pair: Black plays the QID when White avoids the Nimzo with 3.Nf3 instead of 3.Nc3. Fianchetto the queen's bishop to b7 (or even ...Ba6 to challenge White's c4 pawn) and contest the long diagonal.</p><p>Anatoly Karpov played the QID his entire career. Combined with the Nimzo, you have a complete vs-d4 repertoire that works against any sensible White setup.</p>",



      annotated: [



        { move: '1.d4',   note: 'Standard.' },



